<p><strong>Dragon Greatclaw</strong> is a&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Colossal Weapons" href="/Colossal+Weapons" target="">Colossal Weapon</a>&nbsp;in&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The&nbsp;<strong>Dragon Greatclaw</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a>&nbsp;and is a good&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a>&nbsp;for going against dragon-like creatures and enemies. In addition to general Physical Damage, what makes this weapon great is that it does Lightning Damage which can be especially effective towards specific enemy types.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Weapon said to have been whittled from the claw of a great, ancient dragon, wielded by grotesque Tree Sentinels who yet serve the Erdtree.</em></p> 
 <p><em>The claw is enwreathed with lightning, and tears through the dragons' feeble descendants with ease.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Dragon Greatclaw in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Dragon Greatclaw weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Dropped by the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Draconic Tree Sentinel" href="/Draconic+Tree+Sentinel" target="">Draconic Tree Sentinel</a>, fought at&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Capital Outskirts" href="/Capital+Outskirts" target="">Capital Outskirts</a>. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring interactive map?id=2556&amp;lat=-93.71&amp;lng=119.25&amp;zoom=8" href="/interactive+map?id=2556&amp;lat=-93.71&amp;lng=119.25&amp;zoom=8">Elden Ring Map Link</a>]&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Video Location" href="https://youtu.be/HmVjDg4DksA?t=156">Video Location</a></li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Dragon Greatclaw Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Endure" href="/Endure">Endure</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon cannot be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon cannot be enchanted with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic Spells" href="/Magic+Spells">Magic</a> nor buffed by <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables">Consumables</a></li> 
 <li><strong>Dragon Greatclaw</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></li> 
 <li>Deals +30% damage against&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Special Weaknesses#dragon" href="/Special+Weaknesses#dragon"><img title="Dragon" src="/file/Elden-Ring/dragon-icon-40px.png" alt="dragon icon 40px" width="20">&nbsp;Dragon</a>&nbsp;type enemies</li> 
 <li>Deals +15% damage against&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Special Weaknesses#ancient-dragon" href="/Special+Weaknesses#ancient-dragon"><img title="Ancient Dragon" src="/file/Elden-Ring/ancient-dragon-icon-40px.png" alt="ancient dragon icon 40px" width="20">&nbsp;Ancient Dragon</a>&nbsp;type enemies</li> 
 <li>At the minimum 30 str / 14 dex, this weapon has the lowest AR of all equippable colossal weapons, assuming Heavy affinity on weapons which can equip Ashes of War. 
  <ul> 
   <li>At 80 str, it still has the lowest AR, due to its poor Strength scaling.</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;500</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
